WITNESS PROTECTION CONNECTION

2049

The Booby Bar w/i Termi...

Come by The Witness Protection Connection: A Dating Service for the Personae non Gratae and pick up a silk flower that represents your sexual preference: white for hetero; red for bi; blue for gay; pink for lesbian; or yellow for transgendered. Attach it to your backpack, bike, wrist, or wear it your hair if you would like. Then, as you travel around the city during the rest of the week, keep an eye out for another person wearing a flower in your color. If there is an attraction, go ahead and introduce yourself to that person and if that certain chemistry continues to develop, invite him or her to meet you at the Sleepless In Black Rock City Night party at the Booby Bar in the Terminal City Village right after the burn on Saturday night. Pretty romantic, right? Supplies will be somewhat limited so don't wait! Come visit us early in the week for the best selections and the longest/most opportunities to meet that someone special. We'll be right next door to The Booby Bar every afternoon/evening until the party for that night gets started. See you there!

Playa Names/Ice-T @ Identi-T Farm

2165

Identi-T Farm

We will be providing a Playa-Name-giving service, based upon interview, discussion and our powers of empathy, in order to understand the deeper sense or spirit of the individual before us, and reveal their true name within. Any potential name is always discussed and ultimately agreed upon by a quorum of three people before being chosen. Once chosen, a short baptismal ceremony is performed by our very own Master of Ceremonies, a personalized badge is hand-drawn by our resident artists and offered to the person, who then sign or draw their newly-acquired Playa Name in our Book of Names. As with last year, passers-by may also choose to have a Tarot Reading from our resident Witch Doctor while waiting. New this year, we will be offering delicious iced tea to quench your playa thirst. Activities will all take place inside our new dome, where you can relax and enjoy.

Pour Some Fire Down Your Throat

2193

Incendiary Intent

Last year we locked down our little corner of Blackrock City with crowds that extended down the streets in every direction. For our first year as an official camp, bar nights were an epic success. Who could resist? A fiery sign and hot bartenders serving up flaming drinks that scorched the tongue and burned all the way down. For 2010 we're bringing back our classic hot pepper drinks and adding a few more exclusive pours to the Incendiary Intent bar. We kick off the burn on Monday night with an open bar and fire performance, taking in that enthusiasm the first day brings. Lighting up and pouring drinks on Wednesday and Friday, we're sure to get some returning friends and a whole new crowd ready to taste our wicked brews. Fire performers take the stage and dance on the sign.

WoW Addicts Recovery Meeting

2196

Incendiary Intent

Wait, we have to go a whole week without logging in to play computer games? Better believe by Saturday there's a lot of us going to be jonesing for our fix. That doesn't just apply to those of us in camp, there's thousands of people out on the playa that will be getting the mouse-hand shakes by the weekend. Since popping up the laptop and logging on isn't an option, we'll just have ourselves an addiction party instead. Open to all everyone, gamer or not, we'll have a little gathering Saturday afternoon. Anyone who has completed our daily quests, or just wants to hang out and get their fix is welcome. Our resident mad alchemist has come up with some special brews, and servings of delicious chocolate cake are available to all. If any of our "Dragonbreath" chili remains, it's a great time to polish that off. Hang out, drink some "kungaloosh", take down a "sulfuron slammer", and swap war stories of "How I wiped the 40 man raid".

Evening contradance

2606

Contradance Community C...

Contradance every night until dancers or musicians quit (starts after sunset or after burns Sat Sun). Live music - didj, electric fiddle; looped/ trad'nal/ celtic/ fusion/ techno. Fast paced but easy to learn. We will cycle through different levels - you won't have to wait long for beginner level w/ lessons. (And there will be a neighboring dance area for those who prefer to freestyle.) A caller instructs but there is room for dancers to improvise. 1/2 the moves w/ your partner, 1/2 w/ everyone else. No need to bring a partner (dancers swap partners after every dance). Zen is flow, synchrony, bonding (not footwork, not competition). If you are smiling, you are doing it right. Because couples flow through one another in long lines and end up interacting with everyone, it has a very tribal feel–w/ bonding through synchronous stomping, clapping and hooting. It is very playful (variations and flourishes improvised ad lib) and flirtatious. Dancers typically include all ages from children to the elderly, and include people with a surprising range of disabilities. Dancers and callers frequently swap gender roles, and playfully mock gender conventions. The caller gives instructions for each dance's particular repeating cycle of ~10 moves. The basic moves are very easy to learn, but lessons are necessary for advanced moves, and so that new dancers don't become disoriented, and can more quickly get to the point of enjoying the flow. We will use a LCD projector and screen to get dancers up to speed as quickly as possible. While the caller explains individual moves and line movement verbally, the screen will show them diagrammatically from above, and w/ POV video of real dancers from the side. Slippery shoes are helpful. A less than full stomach will make it easier for some to avoid dizziness. Dancers expect to adjust their behavior to suit each person they meet in the line (e.g. just ask for minimal spinning or whatever else makes you comfortable).

In the traditions of our people, we speak of a place called the WHITE LODGE. There is also a legend of a place called the BLACK LODGE, the shadow self of the WHITE LODGE. Zaireeka Party: Experiments w/Sound Revival

2758

Bat Country

Zaireeka Listening Party: Experiments with Sound, Revival Zaireeka is the eighth studio album by the alternative rock band The Flaming Lips. Released on October 28, 1997, the experimental rock album consists of four compact discs. Each of its eight songs consists of four stereo tracks, one from each CD. The album was designed so that when played simultaneously on four separate audio systems, the four CDs would produce a harmonic or juxtaposed sound. The discs may be included in different combinations, omitting one, two or three discs. The album's title is a portmanteau of two words: Zaire, chosen as a symbol of anarchy after Wayne Coyne heard a radio news story about the political instability of the African nation, and eureka (literally: "I have found it"), an expression of joyous discovery. Since its release a fifth disc has been added, adding a new element to the experiment. Leading up to it's release, the Lips would conduct parking garage, and ballroom experiments using car stereos and boom boxes to coordinate massive simultaneous sound experiments using the sounds that would eventually become Zaireeka. I propose to invite any interested booxbox/ mp3player toting burners to bring along their audio device, I will distribute the 5 discs (sets of mp3s) to everyone, divided up into groups, and (huddle into the dome perhaps) for some freaked out sounds. i will act as conductor, signaling when each group is to crank their disc, etc. we can try can waves of volume, mix up groups, or keep them segregated, their are many options left open for these wacky tracks!

2759

Bat Country

According to my count from the burn last year, approximately 96.7% of Burning Man attendees have an LED toy of some sort. I would like to invite rascals to bring their LED toys and submit themselves to my light party. Maestro Matty will conduct a sea of light beings to glow in spectral patterns and pulses. i will arrange participants in the dome and experiment with different compostitions of light. dividing specific colored toys into groups, multicolored toys, arranging patterns, spectrums, simulating starfields, etc. solid vs blinky, elwire, lasers... the combinations are endless.

Nomadic Happy Hour

2800

Camp Nomadia

The vision of Camp Nomadia is to bring together as many cool nomadic spirits as we can to share stories, resources, passion, and community. To foster nomadic community, we are hosting a Nomadic Happy Hour on Tuesday and Thursday (4pm to 6pm) and Sunday (3pm to 5pm). Come and stop by - whether you are a current nomad, future nomad, wanna-be nomad, full-time nomad, part time nomad, domestic nomad, international nomad, technomad, lowtechnomad, former nomad, land nomad, rail nomad, backpacking nomad, open water cruising nomad, friend of a nomad, or you just want to be around nomads. Bring some food or drink to share, and come mix and mingle. Tour a few truly mobile homes. Learn what it is like to live full-time on the road. Ask questions. Swap stories. Or just come hang out and meet some cool folk. Camp Nomadia is intentionally unplaced this (our third) year, so check for our on-playa location at Playa Info (and likely on our website as well) and come find us. Last year we had over 70 nomads from all around the world camped with us, and we are looking forward to another great year in 2010! BTW -- If you are interested in a life of nomadism, come early on Thursday for our "Technomadic Lifestyle Workshop" just before Happy Hour, running 3pm - 4pm.

Tiny Tropolis Mixer

3129

Tiny Tropolis art insta...

Imagine, if you will, a 160 foot long row of 100 identical white boxes stretching out into the middle of the desert. No this is not a mirage. This my friends is Tiny Tropolis. A collaborative Burning Man art installation for 2010's burn that is truly international. We've assembled a crackerjack team of over 100 Tiny Artists from states all over the US as well as from Ireland, England, Canada, and New Zealand. Each artist has their own creative vision for their own Tiny installation and together we unite to form Tiny Tropolis, the tiniest little city of dioramas in the world!

The Crystal Cavern

3136

Above The Limit

Camp Above The Limit's ultimate evening bar lounge chill space is a 40 foot dome brilliantly illuminated with giant (as in up to 18 foot) fluorescent crystals that shoot up from the walls to the ceiling. Colorful mushrooms adorn the inner and outer edges of the dome, and a giant dragon mandala tops the dome ceiling. The Crystal Cavern offers exotic beverages and hand-crafted homebrews nightly. A carpeted space covered with huge, soft, fluffy pillows allows guests to talk, listen to music, or just hang out and watch the colored crystals. Take off your shoes, leave the dust behind, and imagine what wonders lie undiscovered beneath the ground.

Bootie BRC @ Fandango

3137

Fandango

For five years, A Plus D – aka DJs Adrian & Mysterious D, along with Malderor, have brought Bootie BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! Launched in San Francisco in 2003, Bootie was the first club night in the United States dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup -- and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with crazy and creative song combinations, Bootie's DJs celebrate -– and satirize -– the many different genres of music. Bootie mixes and matches every conceivable musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party where everyone feels welcome. It’s a place where all sounds, cultures, and sexualities can unite on the dance floor, providing the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation ... and with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

Swag*Exchange Outpost

3140

Above The Limit

Could I please have a souvenir? Over the years, individuals and camps have become very creative in their souvenirs. We’ve seen some amazing stickers, patches, pins, t-shirts, scarves, cups, mugs, cast metal pendants, glass icons... For those interested in collecting images and ideas to decorate our default world and remind us to smile and remember, SwagExchange is a place for visitors to exchange stickers, patches, pins, and other event swag. We’ll have an honor-system table in the Cityscape Lounge for participants to leave what they can, take what they like, and talk about all the cool stuff they’ve seen. Just like last year, Above The Limit is offering a variety of different and colorful souvenirs, so if you’re a serious collector or someone whose computer monitor or cube wall needs a reminder of something much more fun, come on by!

WoW Addicts Recovery Meeting

3908

Incendiary Intent

Wait, we have to go a whole week without logging in to play computer games? Better believe by Saturday there’s a lot of us going to be jonesing for our fix. That doesn’t just apply to those of us in camp, there’s thousands of people out on the playa that will be getting the mouse-hand shakes by the weekend. Since popping up the laptop and logging on isn’t an option, we’ll just have ourselves an addiction party instead. Open to all everyone, gamer or not, we’ll have a little gathering Saturday afternoon. Anyone who has completed our daily quests, or just wants to hang out and get their fix is welcome. Our resident mad alchemist has come up with some special brews, and servings of delicious chocolate cake are available to all. If any of our "Dragonbreath" chili remains, it’s a great time to polish that off. Hang out, drink some "kungaloosh", take down a "sulfuron slammer", and swap war stories of "How I wiped the 40 man raid".

Welcome home clit-tail Lesbian Mixer

4436

Camp Beaverton

Camp Beaverton for Wayward Girls is your queer oasis in BRC. Join us for an old fashioned Lesbian Mixer in the dessert. We will play our version of Spin the bottle which we call Spin the monkey. Meet your future ex-playa girlfriend in a friendly, safe sexy space. Our dome is women-identified 24/7. Bring your own cup. "Camp Beaverton: Camp for Wayward Girls" is an intentional (and experimental) Burning Man community camp AND conversation. For who? For Gay and Queer Women (identified), Dykes, Bykes, Sluts, Butches, Bois, Trannies, Lesbians, Geekster-Hip Lezzies, Lesbos, Lipstick Lesbians, the Bi-identified, the Bi-curious, the Hetero-flexible, and even (gasp!) the occasional Straight Girl (as long as she's as Wayward as the playa is dusty). We are thouroughly queer, yet inclusive, with a definite chick-centric bent. Participation, inquiry, conversation, and owning your stuff are the name of the game. Our intention is to provide two things: a kick-ass Queer Oasis in Black Rock City for girls who LOVE girls, and a continuing conversation exploring female and feminine queer sexuality in the world and in BRC. Participatory in nature, Camp Beaverton, whether online or on the Playa, is a place where you are encouraged to explore YOUR expression of queerness and allow the rest of us to ask "What is MINE?"

Burn Mitzvah Party

4502

Party Naked Tiki Bar

In honor of the Rites of Passage theme this year, a Burn Mitzvah party is being held at Party Naked Tiki Bar. Join our tongue-in-cheek homage to the age old Jewish rite of passage into adulthood (Must be 21 and over with ID). Sponsored by the "NYC Fetish Tribe", expect an irreverent event filled with fun twists. The Party Naked Rab-Bar will have Rabbis serving Manischewitz. Meet our authentic Jewish Mother, present to dispense guilt and advice whether you want it or not. Make your own Yamulkah or join in a game of Strip Dreidel (beloved Hanukkah game with an adult twist). We will dance the hora, a traditional folk dance commonly known to break out spontaneously during Jewish parties and escalate in speed and enthusiasm to the point of ecstasy. During This celebratory circle dance, random revelers are pulled into the center of the circle, seated in chairs and hoisted in the air by other dancers. Sin City will infuse these age old customs with hedonism and humor and bring to the Playa a RITE OF PASSAGE we like to call THE BURN MITZVAH.

The Crystal Cavern

Above The Limit

Return to Tribal

4527

Above The Limit

Seeking to return the wonder and workmanship our ancestors enjoyed for many generations, a crew of women dressed in leather will cut and move huge logs to an ever-building fire. Wood is placed into intricate stacks maximizing heat and air to yield ultra high temperatures, at the same time creating artistic and inspiring designs. Interestingly shaped limbs are used to form burning sculptures. People point out visions of lizards and dragons they see glowing and disintegrating into flame. For nine hours a three foot wide, twenty foot high column of flame will lick the sky and propel mind and body.

Black Rock Solar Summit

4863

Everywhere

Since 2007, Black Rock Solar has been building solar arrays in Nevada and giving them away at little or no cost. We have built over 1.4 million watts of clean renewable energy in Northern Nevada to date! BRS prioritizes installations for schools, hospitals, rural communities, non-profit groups, and Native American tribes. We’ve also teamed up with other environmental organizations in GREENevada to provide student education and teacher support. At our 2011 Solar Summit, you will meet the staff and crew of Black Rock Solar as well as other Burners doing meaningful and innovative work around the country. Tell us about your projects and learn about ours. The purpose of this event is to bring together all of the different groups and individuals on playa doing work in renewable energy, climate change, environmental outreach and policy. Join us for a cold beer, fresh mint julep, live music, and update from the new Executive Director of Black Rock Solar, Paddy McCully.

Waist Beads Designed by Sapphire

5063

Serenity Giant Game Cam...

Stop by Serenity Giant Game Camp for waist beads to wear on the Playa. For centuries waist beads and decorative chains have been worn by women and men of many cultures. They are worn by belly dancers for traditional Arabic Dance. Egyptian waist-bands were worn by men. African women wear waist beads to celebrate femininity, fertility, healing, spirituality, balancing and energy. The Seven Chakras share many of these aspects—balance, healing, love, sexuality, courage, self discipline, creativity, and enlightenment. Wrap all these wonderful feelings and energy around your waist and wear them day and night on the Playa.

Black Rock Film Festival

5134

Black Rock Film Fest

The second annual Black Rock Film Fest will be presented by the Boston Underground Film Festival and the Engine Theater. Our open air theater will showcase the best short films from around the world to an international audience of art and film lovers who descend on Burning Man each year for fun, art, and experience in the Nevada desert. Black Rock Film Fest 2011 will kick off with a Red Carpet Opening Night Gala before the first program on Tuesday night and conclude with a Wrap Party after the last films on Friday night. Before every screening we will host a cocktail hour at our Casting Couch Bar. The Black Rock Film Fest will also host a live performance from The Zebbler Encanti Experience. The Black Rock Film Fest (formerly known as BRC International Film Festival) began as a collaboration between SF IndieFest and BUFF, the organizations responsible for the annual San Francisco Independent Film Festival, SF Documentary Film Fest, Another Hole in the Head, and the Boston Underground Film Festival. The organizers have collectively produced over 40 film festivals.

BOOTIE BRC: AutoSub

5164

Automatic Subconscious

OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Bastard pop insanity! For six years, A Plus D – aka DJs Adrian & Mysterious D, along with Malderor, have brought BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! Launched in San Francisco in 2003, Bootie was the first club night in the United States dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup -- and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with crazy and creative song combinations, Bootie's DJs celebrate -– and satirize -– the many different genres of music. Bootie mixes and matches every conceivable musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party where everyone feels welcome. It’s a place where all sounds, cultures, and sexualities can unite on the dance floor, providing the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation ... and with free mashup CDs given away like candy! This will also be the after-party/reception for Mr. & Mrs. Z! Come celebrate their union!

Quickie Rites of Passage

5560

This is Not the Camp Yo...

“This Is Not The Camp You Are Looking For” is committed to participatory community building. To that end, we spent time considering the internal gifts our camp has to give, the needs of our community-of-Burners-at-large, the theme that will encompass all of us on the playa this year, and how to make people laugh. Thus, we bring you: QUICKIE RITES OF PASSAGE. The human experience, our shared experience on this Earth, is synonymous with change. The Rites of Passage that all peoples, modern and ancient, have concocted to navigate those changes, deserve a place on the playa. Our camp believes that Rites of Passage, while critically important to human development, need not be painful. Who needs the long, drawn-out pain of childbirth, adolescence or divorce? Go through it quickly and painlessly at our walk-up service for Quickie Rites of Passage! Want a wedding without the stress of planning? No problem! We’ll have you hitched in under 5 minutes. Terrible time as a teen? Painful journey through your mother's birth canal? Awful first day of Kindergarten? Tripped on your gown at your college graduation? Want to be divorced from your playa partner RIGHT NOW? No problem!!! We'll complete or re-enact all of these rites -- and more -- in five minutes or less!" Join us at “This Is Not The Camp You Are Looking For” on Friday and Saturday from 1pm to 3pm. Quickie Rites of Passage will be available on a first-come, first-served basis. Suitable costuming for all rites will be made available by our camp and we make absolutely no guarantee that they will be appropriate -- only amusing.

Contradancing to live music

5696

Contradance Community C...

Contradancing all levels every night to live music - looped/ traditional/ celtic/ fusion/ techno; fast-paced yet easy to learn with a caller who instructs (but with room for dancers to improvise). Sunset - midnightish (later if everyone keeps going), except Sat starts 30 min after the man falls, Sun starts 60 min after the temple burn begins. Kid friendly.

DJ The Mener

5882

Chakralicious Camp

Dance to wildly energetic, funky heavy breaks and house laced with carnival music at Chakralicious camp! The Mener is no stranger to the world of electronic music. Since his first introduction to the party scene in the winter of 1993, he has been addicted to the music. He soon immersed himself in many aspects of the party scene and started breakdancing and doing graffiti, but didn’t start DJ’ing until 1997. Around 1996, he was throwing raves and was opening his own shows by playing his first musical love: hip hop. After seeing how much more the crowd responded to house and breaks, the transition of musical choice was swift and the first emergence of the DJ we now know as The Mener was born. Since his humble beginnings, The Mener has been throwing down funky house and breaks sets in most major cities in the U.S. and has opened for a colossal list of international superstars. Whether it be 50 people or 5,000 people, rest assured this 14 year turntable veteran knows how to destroy dancefloors!

DJ Jocelyn

5883

Chakralicious Camp

Since the dawn of time men and women have been enraptured by the sacred dance, spiraling into the heights of ecstacy and submerging into the depths of soulful bliss. By communing with the vixen within, she channels this energy, adds some sub-bass and creates a gypsy infused sauce of luscious whomp. Like a soft caress down the back of your neck, delicate twinklings of sultry highs lull dancers into a sonic womb, only to be enticed back into throbbing convulsions by another of her glitched out dubstep hip hop/gypsy infused bassy beats Dj Jocelyn promises that she will increase the chance of your evening's coupling with that of sheer wild fun and yum. As the visionary co-founder and producer of Club Exotica she is sure to offer her sexy, gutteral, grinding, liquid-lithe mixes to lift the party's spirit ever higher. She drives your consciousness deep into your hips while furtive, cantankerous, sly, smiles blossom radiantly and dart from your eyes only to incorrigibly drape across your lips.

DJ RobJob

5916

Chakralicious Camp

Come dance to a set of nu-funk and lunar / voodoo / nu-disco, positive, up beat music at Chakralicious Camp. DJ RobJob has been a DJ/re-mixer in San Francisco for last 4 years, having held club residencies at Pink, Shine, and Bubble Lounge. He has also performed for a variety of events (and Burn fund raisers) at SupperClub, Temple, and Mighty. RobJob has also performed worldwide, in Hong Kong, Saigon, Madrid, Budapest, New York, and Los Angeles. He has performed at the last two Burns (at Bassyx camp and Platypus Pussy camp). He has also played saxophone since he was 8 years old, and he is active in the Bay area House Dance community.

DJ Outersect

5917

Chakralicious Camp

Outersect is Rob Rayle, a San Francisco Bay Area based composer and producer of genre-bending psychedelic electronic music that synergizes pyschill, techno-bluegrass, and 70's progressive rock styles. Inspired by sights and sounds form around the world, Outersect fuses acoustic instruments and sounds with digital production to emerge with his own sonic experience. Outersect's "one-man electronic jam band" shows include live keyboard improvisation and sound loops to inspire ecstasy on the dance floor and auditory bliss.

RhythmWave

Dark Side of the Rainbow Showing

6503

Dr Le Tawdry Planet Ear...

We have put together one of the best Dark Side of the Moon/ Wizard of Oz mashups you will ever see. We researched and experimented with many albums to complete the movie. Be sure to stay to The End for one of the most perfect synchronizations in the entire movie! synchronize: To cause (soundtrack and action) to match exactly in a film. synchronicity: Coincidence of events that seem to be meaningfully related, conceived in Jungian theory as an explanatory principle on the same order as causality. This mashup is a sublime example of synchronization and synchroncity. Synchronicity bewteen albums and movies is relatively easy to find. Often times the mood of a musical piece can be flexible enough to fit with many scenes in a movie. But in this case, the mood of the various Pink Floyd albums across the course of the scenes in The Wizard of Oz seem to synchronize with the mood of the movie perfectly. Synchronization is more difficult to find between an album and a movie. Of course you can adjust the start point of a movie to create artificial synchronizations but you would not necessarily expect many other components to align. However, in this mashup you find absolutely amazing synchronized scenes. At the risk of spoiling some surprises ... be sure to pay attention to the music and in particular the timing of the silences after Dorothy's house lands in Oz. Also, pay attention to the ends of songs and note how more often than not the song ends align with scene ends. The synchronizations is so tight it makes you wonder how this could ever be conicidence. Was this designed by Pink Floyd? All band members vehemently deny this. We will have some seating available but you also might want to consider bringing a chair/blanket/pillow. The movie will start at 8:30PM (after sunset when full dark has set in.)

6507

Nyrvana Village

Kostume Kult has been "Costuming the Naked" since 2002 with donations from costume companies, theater groups and burners like you who help us recycle their old costumes and freaky fashions. Here we empower people with new attitude to be birthed down our runway, with the encouragement of our MCs and DJs, onto the Esplanade and into their new lives. The rules are simple. 1. The stuff is free. No returns or barter required although we do encourage recycling old costumes through us. 2. You must wear what you want to take with you. We are not giving "product" but "experience" and transformation is what is being offered-- not a consumerist feeding frenzy. (Decommodification) 3. If you have found something truly wonderful that makes your heart go pitter-patter... Consider giving it to the person next to you. Generosity trumps the accumulation of stuff. (Gifting) 4. If you are looking for something specific, coming in with an agenda, you will not find it. We aint got it. (and we might actually hide it from you! ;) Come in with an open mind to mix and match and be silly (Immediacy). 4. Donated costumes can be moopy. Please help us keep the playa perfect and consciously dispose of all tags, loose threads and packaging. (Leave No Trace) 5. Go forth onto the playa ready to participate and express yourself more fully. Costume is the mix of fashion and theater and the playa is one big-ass stage. After our runway, be prepared to make new connections in your new costumed persona or upgraded burner attitude. (Participation and Radical Self Expression)

BOOTIE BRC: AutoSub

6510

Automatic Subconscious

OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Now in its seventh year on the playa, A Plus D -- aka DJs Adrian & Mysterious D -- bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! With special guest DJs and mashup shows and performances throughout the night, Bootie BRC keeps your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations, celebrating -- and satirizing -- pop culture, both past and present. Mixing and mashing every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly.

Anti M's Home for Wayward Art

6631

Anti M's Home for Waywa...

Anti M's Home for Wayward Art is a place for small art, medium art, amateur art, but especially Bad Art, Lost Art, Found Art, Art which Needs a Good Spanking, and of course, Wayward Art. This is not a gallery, it is more like juvenile detention for art, an orphanage, a half-way house for misfit art. All art in the Home is up for adoption, all the prospective new parent needs to do is fill out a small adoption form and clip it to the Home in place of their newfound art darling. Art may also be committed to the Home, just put it securely in place and say good-bye. While the emphasis is on visual art such as paintings, drawings and photos, sculptural art and trinkets found their way into the Home last year and then found new homes. Daytime only.

The G-Spot Party: The Motel (3 & E)

6841

Campo Alegre

For several years, our camp has presented the Motel which offered BM guests a chance to have fun as well as to entertain their fellow Burners with safe adult entertainment. We have provided a motel motif that includes clean bedding, an ice bucket, and other classic motel environs to promote what adults do in such situations. At the same time, their shadows are projected on the fabric walls to entertain the outside guests with their ‘shadow play.’ This is the perfect melding of the voyeurs and exhibitionists that populate BRC. For many of our previous guests, our motel has provided them an opportunity to do something they may have only dream of prior, but in a playful and anonymous manner. This is our contribution to what we consider one of the most important aspects to a great BM experience; it is not a spectator sport! Also - there will be free CDs - Our gift to you!!!

Tower of Nowhere Day of Celebration

7095

Nowhere Bell Tower (UK ...

After the night of the ritual and theatre of the live bell casting - in an atmosphere filled with chaos and fervour, anticipation and ritual, and a mesmerising display of traditional craftsmanship, and the grand finale of the crucible being lifted out of the fiery furnace and the blazing phosphorescent bronze liquid glowing as it is poured into the bell mould - let us descend on a day of contemplation and celebration!For one day only, the Tower of Nowhere becomes an empty canvas - just like the once unoccupied plains of the Black Rock Desert - here, for you to paint on. Ring the bell, meditate, find your inner peace, perform a ritual, get married, host a tea party or simply read the beautiful messages on the flags which were created by the UK and Nowhere Burner communities.If you have an event you'd like to host, please get in touch.

Tango Milonga @ TUIB

7365

Tangoed up in Blues

Learn how to partner dance with Tangoed up in Blues (Monday-Thursday). We teach tango and blues classes, follow them up with practice time, then happy hour (often with live music), and dances in the evenings. Tango milongas are Monday and Wednesday, Blues dances on Tuesday and Thursday. In our classes, you'll learn how to do these two social partner dances, how to connect with the music and your partner, how to relax, you'll get to meet and interact with your playa brethren, and you'll dance a bunch. During the guided practice time, you'll have a chance to practice during the day and ask questions of the experienced dancers hanging out. At happy hour, grab a drink, dance and chill. Listen to live music if we have a drop-in musician (or let us know if you you'd like to play some blues or tango music at our camp). And then in the evening, dress up, and come dance the night away. We keep the music running at all hours.

Lemon Heaven Dance Block Party

7577

Brand-UR-Ass 'N More

About the fourth day of Burning Man - 2012, God got a little bored. Being all knowing and all seeing, he already had had his Wednesday melt down of too much dust and sun, and needed a pick Him up. He’d taken a liking to Camp Brand Ur Ass, and its Houston contingent, the Rubber Chicken Camp - because Rubber Chickens are inherently funny; almost as funny as giraffes. Anywho, He gave them the idea a couple of years ago to host a Lemon Heaven party - (omnipotent, remember? Sort of like Doctor Who, but without the TARDIS) and knew they’d picked up some lemons, vodka (for those of you wary of mixing), and some powdered lemon stuff, and said, “Yea, verily, thou shalt host another LEMON HEAVEN PARTY!” That was in his most impressive god voice. He also knew they played excellent, party dance music. So, everyone who’s anyone, please join the Rubber Chicken Camp, at Camp Brand Ur Ass, on Thursday evening around 7-ish.

Dex Mex

7876

Equilibrium

It began four years ago as a tiny camp party celebrating home-grown breaks DJ Dex Stakker. Dex Mex (¡Olé!) has since grown to include world-class DJ talent—and perhaps more importantly, margaritas. It has been heralded by many as “the best daytime party all week”. Sure, that could have been the tequila talking, but tequila knows a good party, so you should listen when it speaks. Bring your sombrero, dancing shoes, and a cup and join the conga line from camp out to the party on the playa. If you miss the train, swing by camp for the exact location of the event. Look for the Center of Attention Chair, take a seat, be adored, then come join us for some daytime dancing fun.

PNW Sunrise at the Temple of Juno

7896

Temple of Juno

Calling BC/Washington burners... Vancouver, Victoria, Bellingham, Seattle plus surrounding areas & any of our friends! Wouldn't it be nice to be sure to catch at least ONE SUNRISE? Wouldn't it be nice to share that with the people you know from the default world? That's what WE THOUGHT! An annual tradition, the last several years’ Wednesday morning PNW gatherings have been really great! An opportunity to see many people that you otherwise might not see at any other time during the week... Several people said they really appreciated the callout, as it ensured that they would catch at least ONE sunrise! And it's a sweet time to visit the Temple, mid-week, mid-progress with everyone adding their words & thoughts... Meet you at the Temple, sunrise side, on Wednesday at 6am, & we'll watch the sun rise together. Nice & simple, bring whatever you feel to share, or not! Invite your friends, campmates, associates... & we'll see you there. Wed Sunrise at Temple of Juno, Black Rock City Wed Aug 29, 6am meetup

Black Rock Solar's Solar Playa International

7964

Everywhere

Join Black Rock Solar at its annual event, Solar Playa International. While sipping on a mint julep or ice cold beer, you will get a chance to meet the staff and crew of Black Rock Solar as well as other Burners doing meaningful and innovative work around the country. The purpose of this event is to bring together all of the different groups and individuals on playa doing work in renewable energy, climate change, environmental outreach, and policy. Tell us about your projects and learn about ours. Since 2007 Black Rock Solar has been building solar arrays in Nevada and giving them away at little or no cost, over 2 megawatts of clean renewable energy to date. BRS prioritizes installations for schools, hospitals, rural communities, non-profit groups, and Native American tribes.

The New World Manifesto!

8125

To be determined!

We are on a mission for creative and consciousness-awakening ideas for the ‘New World’. The Mayan prophesy states that we are approaching the end of an age in 2012 – this is a time of transition from one World Age into another. The message they give concerns our choice of how we enter the future ahead. How we cross this threshold will determine how we transition into the coming age.The American nation has already seen a taste of what is to come from other nations, with a gradual decline in standards, increased unemployment and the real-estate and industrial collapse. Coinciding with the ending of the Mayan calendar in December 2012, we feel there is an increased public focus on world events which acts as a catalyst for major change.This project documents the progression of the fulfillment of our objective – collecting entries for The New World Manifesto. Contributions to the manifesto will be personally delivered to the ‘Gods of the Elements’ in Chichen Itza on the 21st December 2012.We are bringing the question to you; How do you want to enter this new age? This project is designed so that people from around the world can contribute to the Manifesto. We will be:-Creating an online documentary series, event log and blog of our voyage.-Uploading content daily that you can comment on and participate in.-Searching for contributors for our ‘new world manifesto’.-Interviewing people from a cross-section of American society.-Filming the ‘making-of’ documentary feature film for release in Feb. 2013.The story is narrated by five leading characters - a cabaret performer, a reporter, an actor, a cook and an artist. They will be Accompanied by the 3 crew members, the cinematographers / photographers.In each documentary episode, the interviewees will be asked about their vision of the ‘New World’ and will be offered the opportunity to enter their wishes into The Manifesto. We are all creating our future right now! So let's do it together!

8156

Root Society

BOOTIE BRC: Root Society Fuck The White Party! The greatest mashup party in the universe comes to Black Rock City ------------------------------------------- ROOT SOCIETY Esplanade & 10:00 12 midnight - 3 AM ------------------------------------------- Spinning only the finest bootleg mashups and bastard pop Now in our 7th year on the playa! ------------------------------------------- Featuring Bootie Mashup creators and resident DJs: A PLUS D aka Adrian & Mysterious D - http://aplusd.net ------------------------------------------- FREE Bootie Mashup CDs will be "gifted" throughout the night! ------------------------------------------- Presented by: BRC WEEKLY - http://BRCWeekly.com ------------------------------------------- http://BootieBRC.com OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Now in its seventh year on the playa, A Plus D -- aka DJs Adrian & Mysterious D -- bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to the Root Society dome in Black Rock City! It's Rootie Bootie! Fuck The White Party! Bootie BRC keeps your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations, celebrating -- and satirizing -- pop culture, both past and present. Mixing and mashing every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco by A Plus D, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

Premiere 48 Hour Film Project Black Rock City 2012

8277

Videogasm

Come to the "On the Red Carpet" Premiere to watch the results of the Black Rock City 48 Hour Film Project! Each of these movies was made in 48 hours on the Playa. "Cinderplaya" features a wizard searching for his Playa love. "Portaman" discovers a mastermind's plan to destroy Burningman. "Sister Lucy" helps Burners learn about sex. During "Abandon All Hope and Fear", a dream teaches the way of the Playa. More movies will be included. The 48 Hour Film Project's mission is to advance filmmaking and promote filmmakers. Through its festivals the Project encourages filmmakers and would-be filmmakers to get out there and make movies. The tight deadline of 48 hours puts the focus squarely on the filmmakers—emphasizing creativity and teamwork skills. While the time limit places an unusual restriction on the filmmakers, it is also liberating by putting an emphasis on "doing" instead of "talking." At Videogasm in Snowflake Village at 8:15 & Edelweiss. Bring your own chair or tarp. Note, to join the BRC 48 Hour Film Project to help make a film, come to the kick-off at Videogasm on Tuesday, August 28th between 3-5 PM.

Eye of RA Party at Osiris Village

8346

OSIRIS

OSIRIS VILLAGE and BLACK ROCK SYNDICATE PRESENT:::EYE OF RA THURSDAY In ancient times, Egyptians believed all forms of life were believed to have been created by RA, the Sun God, who called each of them into existence by speaking their secret names. Humans were created from RA's tears and sweat. The Egyptians often referred to the sun and the moon as the "eye"s of particular gods. RA's right eye was equated with the sun, and his left eye equated with the moon. The Eye of RA therefore, can also take the form of a goddess: the mother who brings RA forth. RA was sometimes said to enter the body of the sky goddess at sunset, impregnating her and setting the stage for his rebirth at sunrise. In the spirit of Fertility 2.0, we must pay homage to RA at night with the moon in full, before he is born again at dawn Friday morning. Egyptian attire is requested for our evening Eye of Ra party. Come as Cleopatra, Marc Anthony, Pharaoh, or any of your favorite Ancient Egyptian Gods and Goddesses to prove your dedication to Ra and be protected until eternity. 8 PM Sophie Rae 9 PM Jonny Quest 10 PM Just J 11 PM Jefr Tale and Str!pe 12 AM Myagi 1 AM Dylan Rhymes 2 AM Donald Glaude 3 AM Hatiras 4 AM The Scumfrog 5 AM Brian Williams 6 AM Dustin Sheridan And your dedication to RA by displaying your Egyptian attire will not go unnoticed, as the Eye of RA sees all. Please find the arm of RA, a Pharaoh by the name of Cameron and he will reward you with a playa gift amulet that would make RA himself jealous. I now bid you safe passage on your way from the default world to our underworld.

THE DECENTRALIZED DANCE PARTY!

8394

Roaming

The Decentralized Dance Party is a portable, battery-powered Party system, with no Central audio source and no Central location. It consists of hundreds of Party People, carrying vintage boomboxes, and a DJ who wears a backpack, containing a powerful FM transmitter. All the boomboxes are tuned into the DJ’s master FM broadcast, resulting in a mobile, synchronized sound system. This Portable Dance Party roams the night, generating complete awesomeness, street by street and block by block, onto buses and subways, into public fountains and beyond. Inevitably interfacing with the public, together we create an infectious epidemic of fun. A Roaming Party Adventure that lasts all night long! And the Decentralized Dance Party (DDP) is headed to Burning Man for the first time in 2012. The plan is to throw a massive, Playa-wide DDP and create a Primeval Party Moment more powerful than all which have come before. It’s likely to be a very good time. THE PLAN: Together, we will create a free-roaming, Open-Source-themed DDP, powered by over 150 synchronized boomboxes, guerrilla sound systems and art cars that will explore and interact with as many other art structures and theme camps as possible, in a full-throttle adventure that rages all over the Playa, from sunset to sunrise! It will commence on Thursday August 30th, at 7:30, at the feet of the MAN, as the sun is setting and conclude twelve hours later, as the full moon Reaches Its Apex and the sun begins to rise on Friday morning... Bring your own boombox, or borrow one from the 150 we will be lending out. ALL THE DETAILS ON HOW TO PARTICIPATE AND CONTRIBUTE AND ENJOY ARE RIGHT HERE: http://bit.ly/PrnJ7b

Alia @ RhythmWave

8793

RhythmWave

ALIA can take a room into deep ecstasy with her bright energy and serpentine movements drawing from her training as a dance performer and her devotion to embodying the feminine, never playing anything that she herself won't move to. She has had a life-long love affair with music and dance - they are her spiritual practice and her most potent passions. ALIA transmits the bliss she experiences in performances to create a connected, alive and activated experience that evokes the sacred and awakens our connection to our source through rhythm and movement. She approaches every set as a ritual and as a facilitator of dance floor unity. ALIA has shared the stage with the likes of Beats Antique, Random Rab, Govinda, Freq Nasty, Marty Party, An-ten-nae, Heyoka, Pussymonster, Sasha Rose, Vibesquad, DJ Jocelyn, and Bay Area favorite DJ Dragonfly. Home on the Grange

8934

BRC3PO

Young food activists are sparking a renaissance of a 150 year old order - The Grange. A national organization having its roots in family farms and community halls. Many Granges have become home to food literacy and sovereignty activists and the slow foods movement. While the Grange has its roots in a fraternal organization from the start it supported woman having an equal voice and vote. The California State Grange is a leader in the Grange revitalization and was an early advocate of GMO labeling. California Prop 37 was initiated by a Granger. California is one of many Granges throughout the country that are supporting a return of agriculture to local farming, organics, sustainable practices, alternative energy and localization of living and working. We actively support the arts, music, education, youth and engage in a variety of community service projects. California Grange is on the forefront of revitalizing this organization that was founded after the Civil War by family farmers who opposed domination by big banks and railroads that controlled markets and prices. Corporatocracy is ever more powerful and many Granges actively oppose it. Come learn about the Grange and how we work to create relevant communities whether urban or rural rooted in family and friendship.

A New Beginning

9081

Truth is Beauty

Men are terrified/traumatized and this is stressful. We are overwhelmed and we are trained to think we are on our own and that we have to fix it ourselves. We developed coping mechanisms to help us deal with these scary thoughts. We fight for control of the universe. Women are terrified/traumatized and this is stressful. We are overwhelmed and we are trained to think we aren't capable of fixing it ourselves. We developed coping mechanisms to help us deal with these scary thoughts. We withdraw and don't try and wait for someone else to figure it out. The fact is we are all living based on a lie. Men, we can't fix it, we can't do it alone and our coping mechanisms aren't working. Women, we are an essential part of the solution - no one can fix it for us or without us and our coping mechanisms aren't working. This is the truth and it's beautiful in it's simplicity and elegant in solution. We need each other. So you see, the Truth is Beauty So let's do it consciously, together. And let's start now at Burning Man... For our daughters, our sons, ourselves we are inviting all of you, everyone, to a group hug: 11 pm at Truth is Beauty after the Core Burn. We hope to see you there.

Bootie BRC: AutoSub

9551

Automatic Subconscious

OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Now in its eighth year on the playa, A Plus D bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! With guest DJs Lobsterdust, Entyme, Faroff, John!John!, Airsun, and more – along with mashup shows and performances throughout the night by Alejandro and Adrian – Bootie BRC celebrates (and satirizes) pop culture both past and present, keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations. Mixing and matching every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

RC Flight on Aircraft Carrier

9754

11 o-clock Trash Fence

CALLING ALL DRONES -)’(- REPORT TO THE FLIGHT DECK The SS Tittyhawk is looking for a few good Burners!!! On the Mornings of Tuesday Aug 27 & Thursday Aug 29, the SS Tittyhawk will be hosting deep play flight Operations in search of John Frum. He has been reported missing and he must be found. Captain Par-K of the SS Tittyhawk invites anyone who has an RC aircraft, to come aboard and test their skills by taking off and landing on the flight deck of the SS Tittyhawk. If you have an RC Airplane, Helicopter, multirotor copter, RC car or truck to please join us out in Deep Playa around the 11 o’clock and the trash fence area at dawn when the winds are the calmest. We will be flying out over open playa so bring water too!!!! Plan ahead and get ready. We will have power on board that can charge your rc batteries if needed. Bring out your aircraft and be one of the first to take off and land on an aircraft carrier out at Black Rock. There will also be a special flight operation that will take the carrier closer to the man and art out on the playa for those who wish to capture video on your flights. The times and dates of this curise is listed are TOP SECERET and will be announced at the Tuesday flight gathering. The Tittyhawk will depart the from 3 o’clock and Esplanade on these dates at first glimpse of the sun and head to the trash fence on the 11 o’clock side to preform these flight operations. --Capt. Par-K

Black Rock Solar’s Solar Playa International

9757

Everywhere Pavilion

Join Black Rock Solar at its annual event Solar Playa International. While sipping on a mint julep or ice cold beer, you will get a chance to meet the staff and crew of Black Rock Solar as well as other Burners doing meaningful and innovative work around the country. The purpose of this event is to bring together all of the different groups and individuals on playa doing work in renewable energy, climate change, environmental outreach, and policy. Tell us about your projects and learn about ours. Since 2007 Black Rock Solar has been building solar arrays in Nevada and giving them away at little or no cost, over 3 megawatts of clean renewable energy to date. Black Rock Solar prioritizes installations for schools, hospitals, rural communities, non-profit groups, and Native American tribes.

Cosmocopia CIIS Community Mixer w/ Richard Tarnas

10064

Cosmicopia

Calling all students, staff, faculty, alumni, and friends of California Institute of Integral Studies! As classes begin back home in San Francisco, we know there are many of us right here in Black Rock City. Instead of meeting in the halls to talk about how "great the burn was this year," and how “we should meet up next year,” let's get together on the Playa to celebrate our amazing community and the unique institution that we call home. PCC Professor Richard Tarnas will give an enlightening talk on the historical role of “heroic communities” in transforming the world (like CIIS and Burning Man). Wear your best Playa fashions, bring your friends and family, and maybe even get some ideas for your next academic paper. Let’s elevate “school spirit” to a new dimension while we enjoy each other outside of our default roles. We’ll have some drinks, we’ll have some laughs, and we’ll dance with reckless abandon as we get ready to transform the (default) world. COSMOCPOIA [address] Tuesday, August 27, 8PM

PNW Sunrise Meetup at The Temple of Whollyness

10202

Temple of Whollyness

Calling BC/Washington/Oregon burners... Vancouver, Victoria, Bellingham, Seattle, Portland plus surrounding areas & any of our friends! Wouldn't it be nice to be sure to catch at least ONE SUNRISE? Wouldn't it be nice to share that with the people you know from the default world? That's what WE THOUGHT! An annual tradition, the last several years’ Wednesday morning PNW gatherings have been really great! An opportunity to see many people that you otherwise might not see at any other time during the week... Several people said they really appreciated the callout, as it ensured that they would catch at least ONE sunrise! And it's a sweet time to visit the Temple, mid-week, mid-progress with everyone adding their words & thoughts... Meet you at the Temple, sunrise side, on Wednesday at 6am, & we'll watch the sun rise together. Nice & simple, bring whatever you feel to share, or not! Invite your friends, camp mates, associates... & we'll see you there. What Is Burning Man Project?

10232

Everywhere Pavilion

Are you interested in what the Burning Man Project has been up to over the last year? We’d love to share our stories with you. Please come visit us at Everywhere on the Esplanade. Burning Man’s outreach groups and affiliated organizations, (The Burning Man Project, Burners Without Borders, The Black Rock Arts Foundation, Black Rock Solar, and The Burning Man Regional Network) have teamed up to create a unified presence on the playa that we call the “Everywhere Pavilion.” Join us in celebration of the Outreach Network! * Everywhere Opening Reception, ‘Party Everywhere,’ on Monday, 5:00 - 7:00pm * Black Rock Solar Summit, Tuesday, 5:00 – 7:00 pm * BRAF Reception, Thursday, 4:00 – 6:00 pm

Scotchfest 2013

10291

Atomik Cluster

Ho ye! Hey, Mukker! You know who you are… maybe not Scottish by birth, but a single malt lover nonetheless. Beautiful scotch, the more exotic and unique, the better. If you understand – really understand – then this year at Burning Man, we may just have an event worth crossing the playa for. Bring a bottle of your favorite drop to the Mystikal Misfits bar (4:30 & B) at 2 pm, Wednesday, August 28th. Come armed with a strong thirst (if not an obsession) for rare single malts – the kind of bottlings that spark rave reviews and win awards. Nothing blended, nothing commonplace. Caress to impress with a spectacular scotch you’d like to turn the playa onto. Once inside our exclusive event – NO BOTTLE, NO ENTRY – you will partake of Scottish music and nibbles with like-minded desert kiltsmen and women. So while spewing feathers in the heat of the day, don’t be a numpty and end up blustered from just any bad swally and scran… Settle into a little Misfit hospitality and savor the kind of “cargo” cults were actually started over… You know at least one of the scotches will be spectacular, because you’re going to bring it. And a dram good time will be had by all! Entry requires a bottle of unique single malt scotch (no blends) , where you'll join other like-minded fans for a once-in-a-playa tasting they'll write bagpipe songs about.

Body Acceptance Dance Party

10314

Silicon Village

The Body is Not an Apology is extending it's reach to Black Rock City in collaboration with Artisans Theatre Collective. This Body Acceptance Dance Party is a chance for all of us to let loose without feeling like we're being compared to the impossible commercial standards we face in the default world. Start the week off feeling fabulous about yourself with a playlist that includes Queen Latifah, Li'l Kim, Salt-N-Pepa, DJ Kool, Notorious BIG, A Tribe Called Quest and much more! Come and shake what your mama gave you and don't feel bad about it for one second. These are your people, you big beautiful burner! Come and get your body painted as our artist sees fit and take a step to show off your radical self love! Close Encounter

10376

Camp Tetrion

The Tetrion Spaceport A very long time ago, Aliens came to this planet and built a spaceport. They brought in spaceships with supplies, did a little bit of genetic engineering and started what we know as modern civilization. Then they left without a trace. Without its force field, the spaceport reverted to basic elements. In other words, it dissolved. The ancient people of that time did everything to try to call back the aliens and their spaceships. They built spaceports, called henges out of wood, to no avail. They even built a spaceport out of stone. Its remains can be found in Southern England and is known today as Stonehenge. Still no Aliens came. They were missing the technology they did not understand. Well, we have figured it out. They were missing a beacon. Without a Quantum Transducer acting as a subspace beacon the alien spaceships have nothing to home in on. Well, we have fixed that. We built one. In fact, the entire spaceport is one giant beacon, shining like a lighthouse in the subspace frequencies. At 11:00 p.m. on Wednesday night, we will turn on our subspace Quantum Transducer. A spaceship will appear and Johnfrum will return to Earth. He will bring us a message of peace and friendship. He will once again return to Earth and live with us in harmony. We will welcome him with wine, women, music and dance. So be at Camp Tetrion and its Spaceport for the festivities. This will be the real deal! Rejoice! Johnfrum will come back at long last!

Contradancing to live music

10560

Contradance Community C...

Contradancing all levels every night to live music - looped/ traditional/ celtic/ fusion/ techno; fast-paced yet easy to learn with a caller who instructs (but with room for dancers to improvise). Half the moves are with your partner, half with everyone else - so it has a tribal vibe, where the Zen is flow, synchrony, and bonding (not footwork, not competition). The repeated cycles of movement give dancers a long time to catch on. In any case if you are smiling you are doing it right. Dancers adjust their behavior to each new dancer they come to and gently realign fellow dancers if needed making contradancing one of the most accessible group dance forms, with for example mentally disabled, blind, deaf and wheelchair bound dancers at many dances. Friendly to children and adults carrying children. Sunset - midnightish (later if everyone keeps going), except Sat starts 30 min after the man falls, Sun starts 60 min after the temple burn begins. Go to website to 'taste' dancing (including headcam video) and music.

BAAAHS Invasion

10636

Celestial Bodies

The BAAAHS (Big-Ass Amazing Awesome Homosexual Sheep) will invade Celestial Bodies (7:30 Plaza) BAAAHS is part penetrable large-scale sculpture, part mutant vehicle, part socio-political statement, and part gay disco. From head to tail the art car will be 40-feet long and two levels. He will be a cuddly sheep on the outside with a chill den on the inside. The only entrance will be through his rear end.  His party side (the port or driver side) will contain a large sound system and a DJ platform, hidden by his fluffy exterior. His business side (the starboard or passenger side) houses generators, ventilation, passage between levels, and the exit. From all directions, he looks like a big adorable huggable sheep roaming the pastures of the Playa.

Clusterf*ck United

CODAME on The Playa is an Art+Tech celebration that reaches out to the creative developer community on The Playa. Our mission is to bring together artists, technologists, and designers that push the boundaries of hardware, software, and physical/digital mediums for one evening to play and share. If you think you've got that special sparkle in you to inspire others, looking for the ways to get inspired, or just want to play and hang around with like-minded people, join us on Tuesday, the 29th, after dusk at our camp Clusterf*uck United for the dimension of " code" me on The Playa experience.

1st Annual Outpost23 Scavenger Hunt Dance Party

10695

Outpost23

Q: What's more awesome than a dance party in the desrt? A: A scavenger hunt desert dance party! Wait... what is a scavenger hunt dance party you ask? It's real simple! At random points during the dance party we'll pick a category like snowboard goggles. You'll then have to find a burner walking around with snowboard goggles and bring them to the dance party to score points before we move onto the next category. If you get them to join your team, you'll score an additional point per round until they leave. There is even a rumor going around that there could be secret bonus rounds! Teams of any size welcome! Bootie BRC: Fandango

10793

Fandango!

OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Now in its eighth year on the playa, A Plus D bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! With guest DJs Lobsterdust, Malderor, Entyme, Faroff, John!John!, Airsun, and more, Bootie BRC celebrates (and satirizes) pop culture both past and present, keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations. Mixing and matching every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

BRC Museum of Transportation History's Annual Gala

10809

Black Rock City Transpo...

Did you know that Black Rock City used to have a stop on the transcontinental railroad? That an extensive subway system once rolled beneath the Playa? That at one time you could ride a streetcar from Gate to the Temple? None of that is true! But at the Black Rock City Museum of Transportation History, we explore the fictional story of fictional transportation in a fictional historical Black Rock City. Learn about how burners got around the Playa before bikes ruled and art cars amazed. See pictures, models, and artifacts gathered since Black Rock City's fictional founding nearly 150 years ago. Hear from a guide, or if we're not around, take a self-guided tour. Perhaps most importantly, tell us your own stories, or perhaps your grandmother's, about BRC's fictional transportation past! We'll be open during the day (lunchtime to dinnertime) starting on Monday. Our big gala takes place on Wednesday night at 9pm--it's Burner black tie. Come find us on 9:00 near Desiderata! Hope to see you.

Dance in Celebration of Gabrielle Roth

10816

RhythmWave

For those who may not know, Gabrielle Roth passed from this physical world last October 22. She created the 5 Rhythms Movement Meditation which is practiced the world over and her clear outline of access to our bodies and limitless expression through the dance has been an inspiration for much of the world's ecstatic dance community. I am honored to honor her and invite her spirit to consecrate the space at RhythmWave Camp with her words, songs and guidance this one time. We'll dance waves, because that's what we do. We'll move to some of Gabrielle's favorite songs, her guidance (it will be her voice you hear inter-spliced with the songs, offering guidance in the 5 Rhythms) and most of all we'll be together celebrating US as the way to honor HER, because that is what she would wish. Facilitated by Eugene Hedlund

Contradancing to live music

11004

Contradance Community C...

Contradancing all levels every night to live music - looped/ traditional/ celtic/ fusion/ techno; fast-paced yet easy to learn with a caller who instructs (but with room for dancers to improvise). Half the moves are with your partner, half with everyone else, resulting in a tribal vibe, where the Zen is flow, synchrony, and bonding (not footwork, not competition). If you are smiling, you are doing it right. Sunset - midnightish (later if everyone keeps going), except Sat starts 60 min after the man falls, Sun starts 2 hours after the temple burn begins. Kid friendly.

Wheel of Fortune

11060

Wheel of Fortune

There is a wheel in the desert, unlike any other. This wheel contains YOUR fortune, YOUR future, YOUR fate…Come to the WHEEL OF FORTUNE! This is where your Hero's Journey begins. The Wheel of Fortune is an interactive divination tool made up of 22 doors featuring unique photographic interpretations of the Major Arcana cards of the Tarot. Inside you’ll find an elaborate gazebo, fire chandelier, and central seating made from salvaged materials. Silk Road Travelers, Card Readers, Gypsys, Oracles, and Destiny Seekers…come muse within. We offer this space as a sanctuary for self-reflection, exploration, universal connection - a Divine Refuge day and night for all citizens of Black Rock City! Join us for our Nightly Midnight Romps with fire, ceremony, song and dance... Be brave, Hero…. Your destiny awaits. Which door will YOU choose? Or which will choose you?

Sunset Celebration-Nightly DrumCircle Extravaganza

11509

Red Lightning

Black Rock Portrait Project Art Gallery Opening

11582

Whiskey and Dust

Join us at the Black Rock Portrait Project "Art Gallery" at Whiskey & Dust 5:30pm-7:30pm on Wednesday. Meet the Artist, oil painter M Vlasic, get "shot", & see oil paintings of the citizens of Black Rock City (and other paintings by the artist). The artist will be taking more photographs of Burners at the opening, some of which may become oil paintings... Will YOU be the next subject? Wine served. What is the Black Rock Portrait Project? It is a series of oil paintings of the “Children of the Dust”, the people of the Burning Man community. The people at the event are very unique, not just in their commonly outrageous dress (or undress) but their countenance, their demeanor, is unique to the event. Covered in dust these people have a spirit, a freedom unseen back in the “default” world. Because it is the people that create the event, it is my intention to focus on the individual. The “models” are photographed on-site, (with their written permission) and the paintings are created using these photographs as a reference following the event. These paintings will eventually be shown in a gallery setting hopefully one which will travel the country. A book about the project is also in the works.

Tango for the Playa

11826

Tangoed Up In Blues

Tango milongas are Monday and Wednesday, Blues dances are on Tuesday and Thursday. In our classes, you’ll learn how to do these two social partner dances, how to connect with the music and your partner, how to relax, you’ll get to meet and interact with your playa brethren, and you’ll dance a bunch. During the guided practice time, you’ll have a chance to practice during the day and ask questions of the experienced dancers hanging out. At happy hour, grab a cup of tea, dance and chill and watch the dome light up. Listen to live music if we have a drop-in musician (or let us know if you you’d like to play some blues or tango music at our camp). And then in the evening, dress up, and come dance the night away. We keep the music running at all hours.

Worldly Wines Happy Hour

12053

Vines Without Borders

Vines Without Borders (Vines) is a global wine bar and lounge inviting guests and wines from around the world to convene for an unforgettable burn. Whether you’re an enophile (lover of wine) or a neophile (lover of new things) Vines is the first ‘port of call’ on your Caravansary journey. Our inviting venue features a lively lounge furnished with vintage couches and chairs, illuminated with LED lighting, showcasing a sleek LED back-lit bar designed and built especially for this burn. The Vines international wine theme is our unifying principle for global community and festivity. We will craft an intimate, interactive experience that provides opportunity for people from everywhere to drop in and enjoy discovering others on a deeper level, making connections that survive beyond the week. Our desire to connect stems from experience with our previous Camp Dawdle where we offered adventure rides on the Wheel of Passage. Guests loved the randomness and fun of the wheel rides, gave many thank-you hugs, but quickly moseyed on their merry way. It was unfortunately a fleeting interaction model. We felt we met many great souls but didn’t get to know any of them. With our new Vines concept, we increase our ‘stickyness’ with a cool wine lounge and an emphasis on international guests. Our wine focus and casual setting invites conversation while unavoidable language barriers ensure focused interaction, commitment to the moment and ultimately greater intimacy. Vines will bring together burners from around the world to make global connections around a unifying theme of wine. In the spirit of Caravansary we will be a multicultural hub of interaction and wine sharing. We’ll enjoy the melody of world languages spoken throughout our camp and across our bar. Of course, we’ll also howl at our own grammatical gaffes while we resort to hand waving to articulate our most earnest points. What we’ll enjoy most will surely be the communion of the raised wine glass as we toast one another.

Bootie BRC: Decadent Oasis

12249

Decadent Oasis

OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Special DAYTIME mashup party! Now in its 9th year on the playa, A Plus D bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! With guest DJs Lobsterdust, Entyme, Faroff, Airsun, and more – along with mashup shows and performances throughout the night – Bootie BRC celebrates (and satirizes) pop culture both past and present, keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations. Mixing and matching every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

Bootie BRC celebrates (and satirizes) pop culture both past and present, keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations. Mixing and matching every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

There will be occasional bellydancers to entertain you, and you're welcome to play in our booty appreciation station and celebrate your love for boobies with our lovely rainbow boobs sign. This is a place to relax and rejuvenate before the sun goes down. We also have planned events throughout the week. Please check the What, When, Where for more information, or come ask us what we have going on.

Black Rock Solar's Solar Playa International

12632

Everywhere Pavilion

Join Black Rock Solar and Snow Koan Solar at its annual playa event Solar Playa International. While sipping on a mint julep or ice cold beer, you will get a chance to meet the staff and crew of Black Rock Solar as well as other Burners doing meaningful and innovative work around the country. The purpose of this event is to bring together all of the different groups and individuals on playa doing work in renewable energy, climate change, environmental outreach, and policy. Tell us about your projects and learn about ours. Since 2007 Black Rock Solar has been building solar arrays in Nevada and giving them away at little or no cost. To date BRS has built over 5 megawatts of clean renewable energy. BRS prioritizes installations for schools, hospitals, rural communities, non-profit groups, and Native American tribes.

The Nevada Burners Photo Shoot - 150 Years!

12783

The Man (6:00 side)

The 2014 Nevada Burners Photo Shoot - 150 Years! Please bring and join your fellow Nevada Burners for this fifth annual group photo at 4pm SHARP on Thursday August 28 at The Man (6:00 side) in Black Rock City. This year's photo will notably be a "Signature Nevada 150 Event" in celebration of Nevada's Sesquicentennial as a state. The group photo will be freely available to download following the Burning Man event, and you can still see the photos of previous years, all here: http://tinyurl.com/nevadaburnersphotos The photo will be also be included in the Nevada Sesquicentennial Celebration Report presented to the Governor and filed in the Nevada State Library and Archives. Join a hallmark of Nevada history. Please share widely. And don't be late! More on the Nevada Sesquicentennial here https://www.nevada150.org/

Mateada with Gauchos del Fuego

13037

Argentina: Gauchos del ...

The idea is to represent the typical "Mateada" that is similar to Hookah but instead of tabaco we use yerba mate and instead of fire we use hot water for "Mate" and cold water or any juice for "Tereré". Is typical to gather around a fire, in a table, a plaza or any public space with friends, family and people in general to share this natural, revitalizing and energetic drink.

Playa Justice

13062

Dusty Justice

Everybody loves to sue everybody else in the good old U.S. of A! So we here at Camp Dusty Justice are celebrating that practice and bringing an open, slightly impartial, fun venue for Burners of all stripes to get their dusty dirty day in court. Our camp will feature a sultry judge (with a real law degree!) known for her fairly fair and reasonably reasonable decisions. If you are convicted or found liable, you can accept her sentence, which is guaranteed to be interesting or you can try your luck at the wheel of punishment. Or you may win your case and see your opponent subjected to Playa justice. Either way, someone always pays! Whatever the choice or the outcome, you can be assured of an unbalanced hearing…for the Playa, that is. Bring your case! You will be heard! Is it your noisy neighbor? A spat with a girlfriend? Did a campmate drink your last cold beer? Maybe it was just your turn to drive the art car. Whatever the dispute, our jurist will sort it out. We will hold court twice during the week or if an emergency arises. Join us Wednesday afternoon and Friday afternoon from 3-5 for fun, laughs, and some serious judgments and some wicked punishments.

Salon 7 - Twilight Tequila

13065

Salon 7 (with Do More ...

Salon 7 - 8:15 & B Join us on your caravan’s pilgrimage through the playa for inspiring and amusing journeys into tequila, beats, dancing and yoga…… A salon is a gathering of people under the roof of an inspiring host, held partly to amuse one another and partly to refine the taste and increase the knowledge of the participants through conversation either to please or to educate. Each of our events holds this definition in heart, whether through poetic infusions of daily yoga, techno and tequila at twilight or the pleasure of afternoon bubbles and beats. • Twilight Tequila Tuesday - 8pm-midnight • Twilight Tequila, Thursday – 6pm – 2am • Bubbles and Beats, Saturday 2pm – 10pm • Daily yoga Jam Tuesday to Saturday 11am-1pm

Meet the makers of the Pyramid of Possibilities

13095

Pyramid of Possibilitie...

Meet the makers of the Pyramid of Possibilities, and learn about all the design, woodworking, electronics, software and hard work that went into it. The Pyramid of Possibilities consists of 56 hexagonal platforms, arranged in a triangular pattern on six tiers. Each platform is surrounded by 220 LEDs and controlled by a microcontroller and an accelerometer. Every platform set at a different height, from 30 inches to 24 feet above ground level. Easy-to-climb ladders on three sides of every platform, fully interconnecting them, providing a virtually infinite number of paths through a 3-dimensional maze.
