Morning Gloryville ~ BRC Edition!

13128

St. Petersburg

"Morning Gloryville - Rave your way into the day!" is an immersive morning dance experience for those who dare to challenge morning culture and start their day in style! We’re on a soul-shaking mission to turn clubbing upside down and transform mornings into something truly remarkable, and you’re invited! Dancing is the ultimate exercise and we humans have been doing it for thousands of years long before treadmills and yoga mats were invented! Free improvised dancing in space (no routines here) uniquely wakes up your body, mind and creativity and will leave you feeling more energized and alive than you could ever imagine. This is a morning movement popping up in cities across the world; invigorating the Wednesday mornings of Tokyo, Barcelona, Sidney, New York, San Francisco, London, Bangalore, Melbourne, Brighton, Amsterdam, Dublin, Zurich, and now, Black Rock City! What to Expect: A yoga space, massage, coconut water, and a high energy dance party to get your day started in the best possible way. Our Morning Gloryville San Francisco resident DJ, Rachel Torro will be shakin it behind the decks all morning! We can't wait to boogie with you in the dust :) *Costumes highly encouraged *No booze *This is a family friendly event!

Museum of Transportation History's Annual Gala

13276

Museum of Transportatio...

Did you know that Black Rock City used to have a stop on the transcontinental railroad? That an extensive subway system once rolled beneath the Playa? That at one time you could ride a streetcar from Gate to the Temple? None of that is true! But at the Black Rock City Museum of Transportation History, we explore the fictional story of fictional transportation in a fictional historical Black Rock City. Learn about how burners got around the Playa before bikes ruled and art cars amazed. See pictures, models, and artifacts gathered since Black Rock City's fictional founding nearly 150 years ago. Hear from a guide, or if we're not around, take a self-guided tour. Perhaps most importantly, tell us your own stories, or perhaps your grandmother's, about BRC's fictional transportation past! We'll be open during the day (lunchtime to dinnertime) starting on Monday. Our Burner "Black Tie" Gala takes place on Wednesday night at 9PM. Fancy wine, cheese, and more! Come find us on 9:00 near Isfahan behind the museum.

Burning Man along with the Regional Network, Burning Man Arts, Burners Without Borders and Black Rock Solar invite you to their annual celebration at Everywhere Pavilion, as we kick off what promises to be an amazing week. Why? Because we are EVERYWHERE and we have amazing global stories to share with you!

Contradancing to live music

13451

Contradance Community C...

Contradancing all levels to live music - looped/ traditional/ celtic/ fusion/ techno; fast-paced yet easy to learn with a caller who instructs (but with room for dancers to improvise). Half the moves are with your partner, half with everyone else, resulting in a tribal vibe, where the Zen is flow, synchrony, and bonding (not footwork, not competition). If you are smiling, you are doing it right. Kid friendly. Possible for many disabled. No need to bring your own partner. Everyone who shows up should have a good time.

Last Bar on Earth/First Bar on Playa

14513

Trash Fence

Last Bar on Earth or First bar on Play, depending on which way you reach the trash fence. Located along the fence, like a mirage looming in the distance, out of the desert, from the dust: Ice Cold Margaritas. The Last Bar on Earth, past the Esplanade, past the Man, past the Temple… as far as a person can go in Black Rock City. …or… The First Bar on the Playa; depending on which way you are coming to the bar. For those trekking across the barren wasteland, evading the dozen or so security and law enforcement agencies, avoiding detection by radar and heat sensors, struggling to finally reach the perimeter fence; our Bar is there to offer you an ice cold beverage and welcome you Home with a hug, brother/sister, before contacting the proper authorities and turning you over to security. For several years I have rode my bicycle with trailer out to the furthest point in Black Rock City with all the booze, juice, water, soda and ice I could fit in the 3 large ice-chests. I purposely set up at the remotest spot I can find, away from camps, sound systems, art vehicles and crowds. Trying to provide a service to intrepid playa explorers, people out riding bikes along the trash fence, those reaching beyond the EDM to see the desert vastness. As they spot our stack of coolers along the fence, in they trickle and find Iced Cold Margaritas waiting for them. Every year we go through every drop of beverage we can carry out there, usually in under an hour or two. Hosted by Camp Threat. Bring a cup and witty banter. Join us at the fence. And, YES, most definitely, Daft Punk will be playing.

Free Photography Zone, Portraits on the Playa

14722

Free Photography Zone

My camp, the Free Photography Zone, has been doing portraits of the participants of Burning Man continuously for the past 19 years. Each person, or group, is photographed in a studio setting and given an instant print as their tangible reminder of their Burning Man experience. I then photograph then on medium format black and white film so that, if they wish, they can get prints at a later date. These are not a re-do of your high school yearbook portrait just in Burning Man attire. I try to give each person enough time to help me make a lasting photograph. On our gallery walls in our shade structure there are black and white prints ranging in size from 16x20" to 4x5' that I hope will be of some inspiration to you. Though I try not to duplicate what I have done in the past they may serve as a jumping off point for our photography session. Not the easiest thing given the approximately 47,000 black and white negatives done so far. I have never counted and see no reason to start now. I consider the people I photograph as the most important part of any photograph and always try my best to make a photograph that will be of lasting value and interest well beyond the moment of its creation. Come, join me, and together we may make something wonderful. I usually begin each day about 10 or 11 AM and continue into the night till I can't keep on my feet any longer. Weather permitting I'll begin on Sunday August 30th through Saturday September 5th. I do look forward to photographing you.

Clown Trauma Support Group

15137

HOTD - Hair of the Dog

It has happened to us all. You're having a great time, easy and happy, dancing through the weeds of your own small life, and suddenly -- a clown. He's trying to be funny at you. He's a burlesque. Or a Bozo. Or a body comedian. You can't punch him because that would be wrong. You can't cry because you're terrified. And you can't laugh because the life has been sucked out of you. So you push it down, deep inside. Where the clown trauma festers in its own silent and pressurized tank of suppressed rage and fear. These incidents have been seen with increasing frequency as clowning has infiltrated our community. Clowns are easy. Clowns are anonymous. Clowns are everywhere. And clowns are dangerous. They are the death knell of participation culture, just as the deadbeats were the death knell of hippie culture. They embody the cheap, the quick, and the easy, and they should not be allowed to take over. Come to our shaded bar and snack on our snacks with us. Learn the story of clowns, past, present, and future. Drink your health in a clown-free zone. Crush the red nose of clown oppression. And embed a new mantra into your soul: I will never be clowned again.

BOOTIE BRC 10-Year Anniversary Mashup Party

15141

Automatic Subconscious

OMG! MUSIC WITH WORDS! Now in its 10th year on the playa, A Plus D bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous bootleg mashup party, back to Black Rock City! Bootie BRC celebrates (and satirizes) pop culture both past and present, keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations. Mixing and matching every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched by DJ duo A Plus D in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.

ShangriLa

Black Rock Solar’s Solar Playa International

15456

Everywhere Pavilion

Join Black Rock Solar at its annual event Solar Playa International. While sipping on a cool libation, you will get a chance to meet the staff and crew of Black Rock Solar as well as other Burners doing meaningful and innovative work around the country. The purpose of this event is to bring together all of the different groups and individuals on playa doing work in renewable energy, climate change, environmental outreach, and policy. Tell us about your projects and learn about ours. Since 2007 Black Rock Solar has been building solar arrays in Nevada and giving them away at little or no cost. To date, BRS has built over 5.5 megawatts of clean renewable energy. BRS prioritizes installations for schools, hospitals, rural communities, non-profit groups, and Native American tribes.

Pinhole Project

15735

Illumination Village

The Pinhole Project exposes 30 x 40 inch sheets of light sensitive gelatin silver paper. We work with 12 pinhole cameras, created out of 50-gallon cardboard barrels. This size is uniquely suited for capturing the incredible scale and immense diversity of art and culture at Black Rock City. Under the red safelights of the darkroom, photosensitive paper is inserted into the camera body. Exposures range from 40 to 300 seconds, where concentrated beams of sunlight are funnelled through the pinhole and into the camera, creating a negative image of the recorded subject. We maintain a desert darkroom in a shipping container, where we gather to processes, develop and fix about one hundred photographs each Burning Man. These unique images are then exhibited in Illumination Village, Center Camp Cafe, and off-playa. The pinhole camp has been creating large-scale portraits with festival participants since 1999. The pinhole came about of the desire of four first time participants to contribute in a unique and lasting way to the ephemeral pleasures of the playa. As we have grown, so too has our belief that this device is the reason that we make our annual pilgrimage. As we have evolved, so too has the camera, not only in functional and technical capabilities but also in its role as a seed of meaningful engagement with other participants.

Flirt Camp Lounge & Bar with Flirty Games

15881

Flirt Camp

Flirt Camp is a lush and sensual lounge space with music, benches, pillows, an alter and a bar. We have a nice backlit Flirt Camp sign on the front of our lounge space that brings folks in. Just park the bike in the provided bike rack and come on in! Once at the bar, roll the Flirt Dice or have a spin of our Flirt Wheel to "break the ice" and enjoy a refreshing cocktail. Mingle in our well-shaded lounge with lots of sensual color and creature comforts. The lounge area is open 24 hours a day. The bar area is open for most of the day while a camper is available. During the week, we hold guided meditations and yoga at the camp, a couple really cool dance parties and a flash-mob in our front yard. The foundation of our interaction with the Burning Man community is a commitment to having amazing relationships and keeping the chemistry alive and hot. xoxoxoxox

2015 Rock Star for a Day Celebration

15960

Beginning at Mobility C...

Nominees were accepted. Candidates were discussed. A Rock Star was chosen. The 2015 Rock Star for a Day is Dani “Rat Lady” Moore! Dani Moore has been the ring leader and endless spokesperson for Mobility Camp. Dani has helped spread word and expand knowledge about Mobility Camp’s goals and mission to build awareness and improved alternative abled access at Burning Man. Dani is an incredible, living example of Burning Man’s radical inclusion principle. She is an inspiration and crates a lasting impact on our culture, maternally calling for inclusive accessibility and consciousness by us all. Help us celebrate by participating in her Rock Star day with her! You can't make the event? * Search your local craigslist for Dani's Wish List items and drop them by Mobility Camp at Center Camp: -- A gas powered golf cart with hand controls: to borrow for Burn or to own -- Knee Scooters -- Wheelchairs *with foot rests* all sizes, in particular XL/Bariatric -- Crutches of all sizes; most needed size 4’6”-5’2” & 5’1”-5’9” -- Walkers of all sizes -- Handcycles to borrow for Burn -- Photographer to capture Mobility Camp activities Dani will receive playa rock star treatment Thursday afternoon, including transportation and soulful beats via her "limo" the Charlie the Unicorn art car (Yay, thank you Unicorn Crew!) Come join in on the fun anytime! Radically Inclusive! Join Us! Everyone's welcome to hug the rock star, jump into the limo and participate! 12:00pm Arrive at Mobility Camp, Center Camp Inner ring/6:00 Present Dani Moore with her Rock Star status. 1:00pm All participate in the accessibility obstacle course 1:45pm Transport Dani and anyone else to Kostume Kult for rock star outfitting 6:45 & Esplanade 2:45pm Limo departs for an out on open playa adventure to be announced 3:00pm Special thank you surprise. 3:45pm Rock Star Charlie the Unicorn limo returns Dani and everyone else to Mobility Camp!

"Now we dance! Now we fight" Dance/Fight! Party!

16778

Skrambles**!*

Come dance, (pillow) fight, and dance again on rapid rotation to high-energy flamenco according to the whims of our Dancefightmeister B Riles! Also, drinks during intermissions. It started with a vision. A vision of Germans in a slightly alternate dimension. A dimension where the only way to dance to German techno was under the strict supervision of a leader. The leader would announce "And now we dance!" and they dance dance dance, only to be followed by "And now we fight!" whereupon a raging fist fight would break out. Soon enough, the leader barks "And now we dance!", fists are dropped, and they stomp dance once more. It was a very silly vision. And now we bring this vision to you. Join us and alternate between internal states of joy and (joyful) rage as rapidly as we alternate between dancing and (pillow) fighting. Pillows provided.

Naked Philosophy

17090

Gymnasium

Nudity has the power to surprise and shock, yet why, on reflection, can something as mundane as the naked body inspire simultaneously so much passion and revulsion? To be naked in 21st century western society demands intense self-examination, the questioning and reappraisal of conventional conventions and morality. In this sense, naturism, as the cultural and political movement of nudism is often known, is an inherently philosophical practice. And what better way to do philosophy than naked? We’re sure your college seminars would have been much more fun nude. Come and join us for lively discussions, debates and story-telling. We’ll be discussing naturism, body image, sharing experiences, debating body modification, if and how laws should be changed – really everything related to the human body.

False Profit's Tuesday Night Party

17150

Illumacanth

False Profit, Inc., sent shock waves through the stock market with its recent announcement of current plans for its annual Tuesday Night Party (TNP) at The Burning Man Arts and Culture Festival. In a move outside experts are hailing for its boldness and freshtasticness, False Profit, Inc., released news that it would be holding the event not at its desert research field campus proper, but “out in the open.” “For 14 years, we’ve invited shareholders to our desert campus to celebrate with us,” said Jef Pearlman, Senior VP of Auditory Logistics. “This year, we decided to think ‘outside the camp.’” Citing ever-increasing attendance, bicycle parking challenges, and the desire for attendees to experience high fidelity sound “en plein air” as forces pushing the party into the open playa, , a spokesperson for the company enthusiastically predicted that this year’s TNP would be “the best evar.” Referring to the unanticipated relocation, an unnamed insider also hinted that the main research facility is so filled this year with mad science projects--which shareholders will undoubtedly wish to keep a watchful eye on as conditions evolve--that the decision to shift was “easy peasy”. The party will be held on the open “playa” approximately 300 feet out from the company’s primary campus location of 5:15 and Esplanade. This location was chosen due to the giant deep sea fish that will be located there, which analysts expect will protect attendees from wandering shirtcockers, newbs, darkwads, those rich people who are destroying Burning Man, and other unsavory characters. Known as Illumacanth, the fish will delight and astound party attendees with its spikes, lights, and fire. Sound for the event will be provided by the legendary Dr. Brainlove, a project of The Phage, a long-time affiliate company and co-conspirator of False Profit.

SCOTCHFEST

18184

Mystikal Misfits / Naar...

Yo, Mukker!! Still kickin’ y’self for missing last year, eh...? 100 bottles of single malt on the bar and you weren’t there!? Like a nightmare you can’t wake from. Except, you CAN... ‘Cause we’re doin’ it again! That’s right, Scotchfest is back -- your basic confluence of peat, dust, and obsessed freaks like you! The rules are simpler than golf, so pay attention... Bring a bottle of your favorite drop to the Mystikal Misfits bar (4:30 & B) at 2 pm, Wednesday, August 31st. MALT FESTIVAL, jocko – exotic, unique, transcendent -- and we’re looking to learn what YOU like. In return, every other souser presents a bottle of their best game, so make no other plans until 6 pm. Be prepared for Scottish music, savory nibbles, and a superlative group of like-minded Burner scotch freaks! They don’t do this kind of thing where you live, boyo, so mark it down. And remember, it’s an exclusive event -- NO BOTTLE, NO ENTRY. So, if you’re tromping through the desert stour spewing feathers like a twally, know that Lassie or Laddie, skuddy roaster or minted dobber, we’ll be gettin’ belter blootered at the Misfits, mate... If you ain’t geein it yaldy, hell slap it intae ye! And as we’re fond of saying, “A dram good time will be had by all!”

Guild Workshops Masquerade Procession & Opening

18437

Procession from Everywh...

Guild Workshops Masquerade Procession & Grand Opening All are invited to the Grand Opening of the Guild Workshops in the piazza at the Man Base! Join us as we celebrate the confluence of artists, makers, tinkerers, and craftspeople from across the world! Among these modern day maker spaces conceived in the spirit of the Renaissance you’ll find glassblowers, blacksmiths, dreamers, chainsaw-wielding portrait makers, musicians and engineers all beckoning your hands on participation in their craft! The festivities will kick off with a costumed masquerade procession starting at 5:45pm at the Everywhere/Artery Pavilion (6:15 and Esplanade) and leading into the Guild Workshops at the Man Base, where our Guild Workshops Celebration will begin at 6:30 pm. Scotch & Hop: Scotch Bar

18575

Scotch & Hop

Bringing out childhood memories and mixing them in with adult libations, comes Scotch & Hop. Combining the fun game of Hop Scotch with one of the most wonderful beverages to grace the planet, Scotch makes for an entertaining and social area where people from all areas, and even all ages (with Children, being the under-21 crowd,) creating a silly and fun set of events bringing out the child in all of us. The social events for Scotch & Hop take different types and games of Hop Scotch from all over the world, and have people jump around and play various forms of the game. Once a Black Rock citizen, who is over 21, has completed a game, they are invited in for a Scotch or Scotch cocktail. (And usually we include other adult-beverages.) Getting young and old, from all across the planet, together and playing Hop Scotch makes people remember the silliness of when they were kids. Also being able to have children be able to play along in the games opens up the experience to everyone.

Morning Cocktails

19531

Morning Cock n Tales in...

Morning Cock n' Tales is an interactive dome where you can come rest your feet after a long Night or Day on the Playa. Our specialty is morning Cocktails (think mimosas and palomas). We also have coffee for those not wanting to travel all the way to Center Camp and stand in the long lines. Besides our tasty beverages, we offer a welcoming atmosphere, comfortable seating, games, friendly conversations, and journals that we encourage guest to write (or draw) their TALES from the playa in. Each year the journals will make the annual journey home so they can added to and enjoyed again and again... We open when the sun comes up (or whenever we feel like it), and stay serving most of the day (or until we are sick of it), always providing a place for weary burners to rest throughout the day and then kicking up the party at night.

Jerry Harrison, Tina Weymouth and Chris Frantz join him for two more songs. The crew is busy, still setting up. Then, three more musicians and two back-up singers join the band. Everybody sings, plays, harmonizes, dances, and runs. They change instruments and clothes. Bryne appears in the Big Suit. The backdrop is often black, but sometimes it displays words, images, or children's drawings. The band cooks for 18 songs, the lyrics are clear, the house rocks. In this concert film, the Talking Heads hardly talk, don't stop, and always make sense." (thanks IMDB!)

Bubbles and Bass

Naked Philosophy

20929

Gymnasium

Nudity has the power to surprise and shock, yet why, on reflection, can something as mundane as the naked body inspire simultaneously so much passion and revulsion? To be naked in 21st century western society demands intense self-examination, the questioning and reappraisal of conventional conventions and morality. In this sense, naturism, as the cultural and political movement of nudism is often known, is an inherently philosophical practice. And what better way to do philosophy than naked? We’re sure your college seminars would have been much more fun nude. Come and join us for lively discussions, debates and story-telling. We’ll be discussing naturism, body image, sharing experiences, debating body modification, if and how laws should be changed – really everything related to the human body.

Heroes & Super Villains Soul Brunch

20986

Heroes and Super Villai...

Soul Brunch isn't just a party; it's like the backyard barbecues of home. It's like the cookouts of our yesteryears. As your families invited your communities over, as the generations of soul families invited their communities over, so too does the Heroes & Super Villains family invite the Playa community over to eat together, drink together, get to know one another, dance with each other and uplift each other. From noon until sunset, our trained chefs serve up the freshest breakfast burritos on the Playa, accompanied by professionally made craft cocktails. Our collection of international DJs spin smooth beats until nightfall. We also give revelers a chance to clean up with our Soul Power Showers; guests experience the rebirth and rejuvenation of cool, cleansing water sprayed forcefully from our pressurized washer system (imagine a water saving car wash inside our shower areas for guests). Baptised anew, heroes set out on their way spreading positive vibes. On it's 11th Annual Celebration of the Soul Brunch, we were gifted curated sounds from Marques Wyatt, Paul Geddes, Deep Wood, Rafael de la Cruz, David Kiss, Big Daddy & more! https://www.amplfy.me/video/oQDJKzBew
